00:26:04.410 --> 00:26:10.780
And so, you know, we didn't know in those
days, we were too naive to know that you could

00:26:10.780 --> 00:26:13.520
actually just go over budget.

00:26:13.520 --> 00:26:15.159
[laughter]

00:26:15.159 --> 00:26:17.480
And so we were actually stupid fools.

00:26:17.480 --> 00:26:19.580
We were actually hustling trying to make our
days.

00:26:19.580 --> 00:26:20.580
Pshh.

00:26:20.580 --> 00:26:21.580
Anyway.

00:26:21.580 --> 00:26:22.580
So.

00:26:22.580 --> 00:26:24.240
No, we, of course, still do that.

00:26:24.240 --> 00:26:29.799
But there is, you know, there's another element.

00:26:29.799 --> 00:26:37.250
And one thing, there is a certain creativity
to, an energy to moving fast.

00:26:37.250 --> 00:26:43.020
But also that's also actually one great thing
about shooting digitally.

00:26:43.020 --> 00:26:45.760
Because you can shoot endlessly.

00:26:45.760 --> 00:26:47.340
You don't need to yell "Cut!"

00:26:47.340 --> 00:26:52.009
You can just, and the actors love it because
it keeps up that energy.

00:26:52.009 --> 00:26:56.659
So you know, just moving fast I think kinda
sometimes does the same thing.

00:26:56.659 --> 00:27:03.190
But there's another aspect to this particular
film in that, I mean, there's, we like the

00:27:03.190 --> 00:27:04.190
cheesiness.

00:27:04.190 --> 00:27:05.190
You know?

00:27:05.190 --> 00:27:11.620
It wouldn't have been, I don't think, certainly
not any better and probably not as good if

00:27:11.620 --> 00:27:12.620
it had been too slick.

00:27:12.620 --> 00:27:16.900
I mean, we liked the, we were imitating a
certain style.

00:27:16.900 --> 00:27:21.410
So we liked the fact that you could almost
see the strings on the plane.

00:27:21.410 --> 00:27:22.410
[laughter]

00:27:22.410 --> 00:27:25.029
