00:38:46.890 --> 00:38:50.450
as I mentioned before, it's a satire on a
style of acting.

00:38:50.450 --> 00:38:53.070
And so that kind of thing, holds up.

00:38:53.070 --> 00:38:58.349
The stuff that doesn't is, are the lines that
are specific to a commercial.

00:38:58.349 --> 00:39:00.359
Or a television show.

00:39:00.359 --> 00:39:01.490
Or a movie.

00:39:01.490 --> 00:39:02.490
You know.

00:39:02.490 --> 00:39:06.500
And even some of the movies like the Saturday
Night Fever, you know.

00:39:06.500 --> 00:39:07.500
People.

00:39:07.500 --> 00:39:09.579
That movie has held up.

00:39:09.579 --> 00:39:11.710
Is still with us on DVD.

00:39:11.710 --> 00:39:16.809
So to the extent that we pick those movies,
we're alright.

00:39:16.809 --> 00:39:23.220
And I think a lot of times certain things
skirt by that even if you don't know the reference

00:39:23.220 --> 00:39:25.820
it's, it passes.

00:39:25.820 --> 00:39:26.820
You know.

00:39:26.820 --> 00:39:29.480
That joke is going along to the next.

00:39:29.480 --> 00:39:33.770
So but no, we, it wasn't something, it was
something that happened.

00:39:33.770 --> 00:39:37.059
But, and I agree with you, but it wasn't,
it was not purposeful.

00:39:37.059 --> 00:39:38.059
[laughter]

